==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mala
<hw>Ma"la</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos>; <sing>pl. of
<singw>Malum</singw>.</sing> <ety>[L.]</ety> <def>Evils; wrongs;
offenses against right and law.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Mala in se</b></col> <ety>[L.]</ety> <fld>(Law)</fld>,
<cd>offenses which are such from their own nature, at common law,
irrespective of statute.</cd> -- <col><b>Mala prohibita</b></col>
<ety>[L.]</ety> <fld>(Law)</fld>, <cd>offenses prohibited by statute, as
distinguished from <contr>mala in se</contr>, which are offenses at
common law.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Malabar</ent>⟦br⟧
